Am Gerald Alan Ney.  No nickname at present.  Served in the US Army from 11/26/67 to 7/11/71.  One tour in Vietnam, 7/13/68 to 7/13/69 as a 2LT/1Lt Aerial Surveillance Officer with the 172nd Military Intelligence Company, 173rd Airborne  Brigade (&quot;The Herd&quot;) at LZ English, Binh Dinh Province.  Was in charge of an 8 man (when full strength) aerial imagery interpretation section, flew 39 hand held aerial photo reconnaisance missions in everything from Hueys to L-19 Bird Dog fixed wing aircraft and had regular court martial duty for 10 months.  Fortunate to be only shot at once by the enemy in those 39 air missions; though our own artillery made up for it by two narrow misses.  Spent 19 days on detached duty at Bao Lac, specifically for hand held air photo duty.<br><br>
Just turned 52.  Married 25 1/2 years.  3 children, boy-24, boy-23, girl-19 w/same birthday.  BS-Geography from University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee [UWM]6/67.  Have been an Inventory Manager with the Navy Aviation Supply Office (recently renamed Navy Inventory Control Point) since Oct '72.  Though born and raised in Milwaukee, have not lived there since entry on active duty.  In Phily since '72, except for 21 months as a field rep at Naval Air Station Alameda, Ca from 9/77 to 6/79.  Belong to several veterans, environmental and neighborhood orgs, and am currently president of my Vietnam Veterans of America [VVA]chapter.<br>
Lector at church, and occasionally participate in services as a musician (Spanish percussion &amp; accordian).  Former French Horn player in HS &amp; Univ.  Am quite possibly stretched too thin on commitment; though I wish it was my body that was in that condition.  Registered as an independent - don't really feel at home in any party these days.  Have always been a bit of a square peg.  <br>

